SIMPLE: jacquard
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jacquard
<hw>Jac*quard"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or
invented by, <etsep>Jacquard</etsep>, a French mechanician, who died in
1834.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Jacquard apparatus</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Jacquard arrangement</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a device applied to
looms for weaving figured goods, consisting of mechanism controlled by a
chain of variously perforated cards, which cause the warp threads to be
lifted in the proper succession for producing the required figure.</cd>
-- <col><b>Jacquard card</b></col>, <cd>one of the perforated cards of a
Jacquard apparatus.</cd> -- <col><b>Jacquard loom</b></col>, <cd>a loom
with Jacquard apparatus.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jacqueminot</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
